article.headline: Austin Peay 79, TENN Wesleyan 64
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) --Fernandez Lockett and Landon Shipley scored 16 points apiece and Austin Peay won its first game Monday night, beating Tennessee Wesleyan 79-64. Austin Peay (1-3) controlled the boards 56-31 and won even though Lockett and Shipley were the only Governors in double figures. Austin Peay also was decisive at the free throw line, making 20-of-31 to 5-of-11 for the visitors. Tennessee Wesleyan (5-3) was led by Tyler Gaskin with 25 points. Mark Riden added 10, making 5-of-7 from the floor. Austin Peay, recording its 1,000th all-time win, led 48-28 at the half. Lockett also had a game-high 11 rebounds.
